I've been coming for a long time. I and 3 others were waiting at the door but the staff was late to open. I'm always friendly w/ the manager, so when she opened the door I said, "Good mornin! How are ya?" She said, "Not ready yet..." I felt like they took attitude. But they were the ones opening late! I know the manager is one short in staff and maybe that's it then. I came to the counter but they were still prepping. I waited about 2-3 minutes. Then I decided maybe another time & I walked out. I sat in front in my car for a while, still thought about coming in, watched the other 3 customers get waited on. And then I left. You don't understand. I come in every morning at the same time! We've all laughed together. They know my order by heart. I just say "the usual" or I switch it up a little bit. Not saying I won't go back, I'll try my luck tomorrow. But I'm in the customer service biz too. I have to be professional and decent to the average public, and then I have to do what I have to do with the rest. They need to watch that, it's on them if they're late opening. A word or two about that is better than what I got. I'm just sayin'. I still like them and the place - that's not the issue. I watch out for them when I'm on patrol, even! I doubt they even know that. But suppose I were new to them? Might I come back? Maybe not!  ijs. They're good people, just don't get attitude when all we want is to come in, get an order and be somewhere for a moment to relax, havee our coffees and enjoy the morning flavors.
